LEGAL IMPLICATIONS
Federal Crimes (U.S.):
18 U.S.C. § 2511 - Wiretap Act:

Unlawful interception of electronic communications
Applies to email, web traffic, messages
Penalty: Up to 5 years per violation
Exception: Only lawful if proper warrant obtained
Francesco's case: If warrant obtained based on fraudulent prosecution, warrant is void
18 U.S.C. § 1030 - Computer Fraud and Abuse Act:

Unauthorized access to protected computer
Exceeding authorized access
Causing damage/obtaining information
Penalty: Up to 10 years
Applies even to government agents if access exceeds warrant scope
18 U.S.C. § 2701 - Stored Communications Act:

Unlawful access to stored electronic communications
Penalty: Up to 5 years
Applies to emails, messages, cloud storage
18 U.S.C. § 241/242 - Civil Rights Violations:

